briefTitle: Risankizumab Versus Secukinumab for Participants With Moderate to Severe Plaque Psoriasis
officialTitle: A Multicenter, Randomized, Open Label, Efficacy Assessor-Blinded Study of Risankizumab Compared to Secukinumab for the Treatment of Adult Subjects With Moderate to Severe Plaque Psoriasis Who Are Candidates for Systemic Therapy
summary: The main objective of this study is to evaluate the efficacy and safety of risankizumab compared with secukinumab for the treatment of adult subjects with moderate to severe plaque psoriasis who are candidates for systemic therapy.

primaryOutcome.measure: Percentage of Participants With a 90% Reduction From Baseline Psoriasis Area and Severity Index (PASI 90) at Week 16
